data.enText: to become, or to make sb/sth become, conscious or healthy and strong again

data.chText: 这些花见了水很快就活过来了。
data.enText: The flowers soon revived in water.
The economy is beginning to revive.

data.chText: 护理人员无法使她苏醒。
这部电影意在使她渐趋衰败的事业再现辉煌。
data.enText: This movie is intended to revive her flagging career.
to make sth start being used or done again

data.chText: 应该恢复这一独特的风俗。
data.enText: This quaint custom should be revived.

data.chText: 她一直在设法再次展开同工同酬的辩论。
data.enText: She has been trying to revive the debate over equal pay.
to produce again a play, etc. that has not been performed for some time

data.chText: 这部20世纪30年代的音乐剧正在国家剧院重新上演。
data.enText: This 1930s musical is being revived at the National Theatre.

simple_means.memory_skill: re 重新 + viv 生命 + e → 重新活 → 复活

example: She revived after the doctor gave her an injection

tr: give new life or energy to
example: A hot soup will revive me
The doctors revived the comatose man

tr: restore from a depressed, inactive, or unused state
example: He revived this style of opera
He resurrected the tango in this remote part of Argentina

tr: be brought back to life, consciousness, or strength

value.def: When something such as the economy, a business, a trend, or a feeling is revived or when it revives, it becomes active, popular, or successful again.

example.ex: ...an attempt to revive the British economy...
example.tran: 试图复兴英国经济的努力

example.ex: His trial revived memories of French suffering during the war...
example.tran: 他的受审重新勾起了在战争中受苦受难的法国人民的回忆。

example.ex: There is no doubt that grades have improved and interest in education has revived.
example.tran: 无疑，成绩提高了，上学的兴趣也恢复了。

value.tran: (使)复苏;(使)复兴;(使)恢复;(使)再次流行

example.ex: Habib grimaced at the revived memories.
example.tran: 重新涌上心头的记忆让哈比卜愁眉苦脸。

value.def: When someone revives a play, opera, or ballet, they present a new production of it.

example.ex: The Gaiety is reviving John B. Kean's comedy 'The Man from Clare'.
example.tran: 盖伊提剧院正在重新上演约翰·B. 基恩的喜剧《来自克莱尔的人》。

value.tran: 重新上演(戏剧、歌剧或芭蕾等)

value.def: If you manage to revive someone who has fainted or if they revive, they become conscious again.

example.ex: She and a neighbour tried in vain to revive him...
example.tran: 她和邻居想尽一切办法都没能让他苏醒过来。

example.ex: With a glazed stare she revived for one last instant.
example.tran: 她最后清醒了一会儿，眼神呆滞。
